channel.title: Murray-Sunset NP NORTH - FLORA - north of Sturt Hwy
channel.description: Including Lake Wallawalla and all areas of the park north of the Sturt Hwy. See also Neds Corner collection.

item.title: Atriplex vesicaria subsp. macrocystidia
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: On roadside. Probably Atriplex lindleyi lindleyi at bottom of pic.

item.title: Zygophyllum apiculatum
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Five petals and largeish, roundish leaves are a good feature combination for ID. Flowering on roadside, probably taking advantage of road verge water run-off. Unusual flowering time according to the books.

item.title: Teucrium racemosum s.s., Theclinesthes serpentata serpentata
item.dc:creator: russell

item.title: Minuria denticulata
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Flowering on roadside. Second pic shows it growing in among Teucrium racemosum.

item.title: Goodenia heteromera
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Spreading Stolons. Seen at two spots on the Lake Wallawalla circuit.

item.title: Calotis scapigera
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Pretty much scabrous, forming large mats as it spreads by stolons. Next to an arm off the Murray (in flood) that leads to Lake Wallawalla. Plants within 10m of the river bank.
